snippet: The Freedom Party, whose candidate, Norbert Hofer, narrowly lost a May 22 runoff, said there were electoral irregularities.
abstract: Austria's far-right Freedom Party of Austria legally challenges results of presidential elections in which candidate Norbert Hofer suffered narrow defeat; challenge is unprecedented in modern history of country.
lead_paragraph: The Freedom Party, whose candidate, Norbert Hofer, narrowly lost a May 22 runoff, said there were electoral irregularities.

headline.main: Far-Right Party in Austria Challenges Results of Presidential Vote
headline.print_headline: Far-Right Party Challenges Austrian Election Results
